cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV

This paper is about a sequence-to-sequence toolkit for Neural Machine Translation (NMT), which falls under the category of Natural Language Processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of different neural network architectures, optimization techniques, and inference improvements, which are related to machine learning and deep learning. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the toolkit is built on MXNet, which is a deep learning framework for computer vision tasks, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper reports benchmark results on two language pairs, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it involves training neural networks.
